content: Bronze sculpture by Singaporean sculptor Chong Fah Cheong 1°17′11.5″N 103°51′08.2″E﻿ / ﻿1.286528°N 103.852278°E﻿ / 1.286528; 103.852278 ***First Generation*** is a bronze sculpture by [Singaporean](/wiki/Singapore) sculptor [Chong Fah Cheong](/wiki/Chong_Fah_Cheong). The sculpture was created as part of a series of sculptures by various sculptors, in the Open Air Interpretative Centre project by the [Singapore Tourism Board](/wiki/Singapore_Tourism_Board). Chong's sculpture was the first to be unveiled on 31 December 2000. This Singapore-related article is a stub. You can help Wikipedia by expanding it. - v - t - e This sculpture article is a stub.
